# =====================================
# Supabase Configuration (Template)
# =====================================
# This file serves as a template for your local `.env` file.
# It contains the variables required to connect the app to Supabase.
#
# ⚠️ Do NOT commit your actual `.env` file.
# Use this template to create your own local configuration.
#
# -------------------------------------
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Run: flutter pub get
# 2. Create a file named `.env` in the project root (same level as pubspec.yaml)
# 3. Copy ONLY the two variables below into your `.env` file
# 4. Replace the placeholders with your Supabase project credentials
#
# -------------------------------------
# Where to find values:
# SUPABASE_URL:
#   Found in the Supabase Dashboard → Project Overview (under project name)
#
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY:
#   Found in Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → anon public key
#
# ⚠️ Do NOT use the service_role key.
# =====================================

SUPABASE_URL=https://our-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=our_anon_key_here